-- Up Migration
-- Issue #500. Rescues the 14 NULL-svg_data family_silhouettes via
-- species/genus-level Phylopic lookup. After PR #499 (#498 build-538
-- re-audit), every family-node lookup either 404'd or produced only
-- license-incompatible candidates. Phylopic coverage is denser at the
-- species node for iconic taxa than at the family-node abstraction —
-- the script tries an iconic AZ species per family, then the genus on
-- species 404.
--
-- Generated by scripts/curate-phylopic.mjs --rescue-via-species on 2026-05-13
-- using the Phylopic API two-step recipe (/nodes?filter_name →
-- /images?filter_node) and the existing auto-pick heuristic + quality
-- gates (license whitelist, real creator, valid imagePageUrl,
-- svgPathD ≥100 chars + ≥20 total path commands; PD-mark rejected).
--
-- The "≥20 total path commands" rule replaces #499's "≥5 distinct path
-- commands" rule, which was mis-calibrated against potrace output —
-- every shipped Phylopic silhouette in migration 17000 uses only M, L,
-- C, Z (≤4 distinct), so the original gate would have rejected the entire
-- production corpus.
--
-- Empirical audit of the actually-shipped corpus (svg_data literals from
-- migration 17000, counting /[MLCQTAZ]/i matches per path):
--   n = 22, min = 3, max = 43, median = 16, below 20 = 13 of 22 (≈59%).
--
-- The ≥20 floor is therefore NOT a back-fit to the shipped corpus — it is
-- a going-forward tightening that fires at curation time, not at runtime.
-- Already-shipped silhouettes are unaffected. The four rescues in this
-- migration have command counts {gaviidae: 25, numididae: 22,
-- phasianidae: 22, tytonidae: 33}, all comfortably above the floor.
-- See the corrected gate at extractPathD() in scripts/curate-phylopic.mjs
-- (with full detail on the audit).
--
-- Rescued (svg_data flipped from NULL → real path-d via species/genus):
--   gaviidae — via genus "Gavia" — CC0-1.0, creator: Andy Wilson, https://www.phylopic.org/images/b6673a57-d8ec-4983-8c64-ab1500794a96
--   numididae — via species "Numida meleagris" — CC0-1.0, creator: Matías Muñoz, https://www.phylopic.org/images/f7200232-d635-4d79-bcaa-a59867376d09
--   phasianidae — via species "Meleagris gallopavo" — CC0-1.0, creator: Andy Wilson, https://www.phylopic.org/images/4bba4e4c-c313-4e35-b55c-a69bd67b7c96
--   tytonidae — via species "Tyto alba" — CC0-1.0, creator: Sharon Wegner-Larsen, https://www.phylopic.org/images/088bc660-44e4-4717-b5fc-13ee15ade62b
--
-- Still NULL after species/genus cascade (rejection reason in parentheses):
--   calcariidae (cascade-exhausted: family=http-404-on-nodes, species=http-404-on-nodes, genus=http-404-on-nodes)
--   cuculidae (cascade-exhausted: family=no-candidates, species=no-candidates, genus=no-candidates)
--   icteriidae (cascade-exhausted: family=http-404-on-nodes, species=http-404-on-nodes, genus=http-404-on-nodes)
--   peucedramidae (cascade-exhausted: family=http-404-on-nodes, species=http-404-on-nodes, genus=http-404-on-nodes)
--   polioptilidae (cascade-exhausted: family=http-404-on-nodes, species=http-404-on-nodes, genus=http-404-on-nodes)
--   ptiliogonatidae (cascade-exhausted: family=http-404-on-nodes, species=http-404-on-nodes, genus=http-404-on-nodes)
--   ptilogonatidae (cascade-exhausted: family=http-404-on-nodes, species=http-404-on-nodes, genus=http-404-on-nodes)
--   remizidae (cascade-exhausted: family=http-404-on-nodes, species=http-404-on-nodes, genus=http-404-on-nodes)
--   tityridae (cascade-exhausted: family=http-404-on-nodes, species=http-404-on-nodes, genus=http-404-on-nodes)
--   vireonidae (cascade-exhausted: family=http-404-on-images, species=http-404-on-nodes, genus=http-404-on-images)
--
-- The full audit trail (every slug attempted, every candidate considered)
-- lives at scripts/phylopic-picks.json under the updated entries. Each
-- rescued entry carries `resolutionPath: "family"|"species"|"genus"` so
-- a future reader can see which lookup path produced the pick.
--
-- After this migration lands in main, the operator runs
-- scripts/purge-silhouettes-cache.sh (#252) as part of the production
-- deploy runbook to purge the CDN cache for /api/silhouettes.

